<h2 id="handling-the-plain-password">Handling the Plain Password <a class="headerlink" href="user-plain-password#handling-the-plain-password" title="Permalink to this headline"><i class="fa fa-link" aria-hidden="true"></i></a></h2>
<p>Here's the plan: we'll start with a plain text password, encrypt it through the
<code>bcrypt</code> algorithm and store that on the <code>password</code> property.</p>
<p>How? The best way is to set the plain-text password on the User and encode it automatically
via a Doctrine listener when it saves.</p>
<p>To do that, add a new property on <code>User</code> called <code>plainPassword</code>. But wait! <em>Don't</em>
persist this with Doctrine: we will of course <em>never</em> store plain-text passwords:</p>
<p><div class="code-block-wrapper" data-code-block-guid="9ab3a502fb">
